Start

Initialize empty data structures to store faculty details, time slots, and workload.

Input the number of faculty members.

For each faculty member:

Input faculty name or ID

Input number of classes assigned

For each class, input day and time slot

Store this information in a dictionary

For each faculty member:

Check the entered time slots for overlapping day and time

If an overlap is found, mark it as a timetable conflict

Calculate total teaching hours per week for each faculty member.

Compare calculated workload with the predefined maximum allowed workload.

Identify:

Overloaded faculty (workload above limit)

Underloaded faculty (workload below limit)

For each overloaded faculty member:

Find suitable underloaded faculty

Suggest transferring a class that does not create a timetable conflict

Generate a report showing:

Faculty workload

Detected conflicts

Suggested workload adjustments

Save the report to a file for future reference.

End
